## 9. Customization Notes

These elements can be tuned over time as more examples accumulate:

- Degree of humor or informality allowed in internal emails vs. chats.
- Preferred sign‑offs (“Thanks,” “Best,” etc.) by audience.
- Level of detail in TL;DR vs. body.
- Amount of context vs. brevity for recurring collaborators vs. new stakeholders.

When editing this file, **keep the overall section structure and headings stable** so AI systems can reliably anchor on them, and adjust only the bullets under each heading as Jason’s preferences evolve.

